fields.titre: Moulay Hafid Elalamy : «La Task Force juge admirable le dossier marocain»
fields.smallTitre: «La Task Force juge admirable le dossier marocain»
fields.contenu: Les membres de la Task Force sont repartis ! Ils n’ont pas fait de déclaration ni donné d’interview à la presse. Mais à en croire Moulay Hafid Elalamy, président du comité national pour l’organisation de la Coupe du monde 2026, la délégation de la FIFA a affiché son admiration pour la qualité du dossier du Maroc remis lors du dépôt de candidature. Le président du comité Maroc 2026 a en outre indiqué que le concept des stades modulaires, les infrastructures du transport, la qualité de l’organisation de la visite et le sérieux et la crédibilité du dossier, ainsi que la compétence et l’implication de l’équipe Coupe du monde Maroc 2026, ont beaucoup séduit les experts de la FIFA.

fields.titre: Bridge Demolished in Controlled Explosion in China
fields.smallTitre: Bridge Demolished in Controlled Explosion in China
fields.contenu:
A video of very successful controlled explosion in China published on YouTube on February 6 went viral on social media.
The video shows the destruction of “the 60-year-old Laoshahe Bridge in central China’s Henan province” in a very successful controlled explosion.
The footage that looks like a piece of art shows 150-meter-long bridge quickly blown up into rubble with dust and smoke went up and the debris sunk in the Laosha River.
According to the Yahoo News, “the bridge was closed after it was deemed unsafe for vehicular traffic between the city of Dingcheng and Huaiyang County.”

Rabat – One Moroccan spice seller surprises German tourists in a video posted by a German Youtuber Yan Anga.
The vendor can be seen extolling the medical uses of his natural wares and explaining their appropriate application to German tourists–in German!
This polyglot yet another example of the legendary Moroccan linguistic prowess.

fields.smallTitre: McDonald’s Kicks Out Customer for Buying Homeless Man Food
fields.contenu:
McDonald’s kicks out customer for buying homeless man food in Myrtle Beach, South Carolina without refunding the guys money.
A kind-hearted guy invited a old homeless man into McDonald’s for food. He bought him some food.
But, McDonald’s did not like the fact a homeless man was in their restaurant. So, they called the police and had both men removed with a “no trespass” put in order.
